@Node "Acknowledgements" "Hall of Fame"

The following people helped me during the development of "CyberView":

@{b}Frank Mariak@{ub}
	He is one of the authors of CyberGraphX, made bug fixes for me,
	gave me	hints, always supplied me the latest version and of course
	tested CyberView.

@{b}Christoph Feck@{ub}
	He gave me an example source for loading pictures with the
	"datatypes.library" and wrote the "jpeg.codec" used to load
	JFIF pictures.

@{b}Jürgen Weinelt@{ub}
	He helped me writing my (unpublished) GIF datatype on which
	CyberView's GIF loader is based. He also supplied me some PCX
	pictures for testing my PCX loader.

@{b}Ralph Schmidt@{ub}
	He gave me the source for a @{u}fast@{uu} planar chunky converter.

@{b}Michael Hohmann, Markus Stipp, Stefan Becker, Stefan Stuntz, Stefan Gybas@{ub}
	They helped me beta-testing CyberView.
@EndNode

